div.p:
For thus, when we exchange this life for another, we shall again be thought worthy of a residence in the heavens, and of associating with all the celestial Gods, whom, now beholding⁠ [
], we ought to venerate with those fruits of which they are the causes, sacrificing indeed to [
] them from all these, when they have arrived at maturity, but not conceiving all of us to be sufficiently worthy to sacrifice to the Gods.
